# Desktop XCUI Lightweight Rules

Scope: applies only to desktop Mac automation Java files (`desktop/mac`), not mobile app files.

- Use XCUI-first interactions only (`By.name`, XCUI class names); avoid XPath in desktop flows/pages.
- Prefer exact-name probes before broad `findElements` scans.
- Keep retries bounded with short polling (tight timeouts, fail fast with debug context).
- Avoid `getPageSource()` in tight loops; use it only as throttled fallback or failure debug.
- For click targets with duplicate text, restrict candidate pools (button/pop-up nodes) to avoid heading/title clicks.
- Add/keep step timing behind a Maven flag (e.g., `-Dmac.timing.enabled=true`) so diagnostics are optional.
